<div class="container mt-5">

  <div class="card mb-4 shadow-lg">
    <div class="card-header text-center bg-primary text-white">
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p>This API offers a comprehensive list of all dog breeds. Each breed is displayed alongside its potential sub-breeds. For instance, the breed <strong>"australian"</strong> includes a sub-breed known as <strong>"shepherd."</strong> This information is essential for storing both breeds and their sub-breeds in our database.</p>
      <p><strong>Table:</strong> <code>Breeds</code></p>
      <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Columns:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><code>name</code> - Contains the name of the breed (e.g., <strong>"australian"</strong>)</li>
            <li><code>sub_breed</code> - Contains the name of the sub-breed if it exists (e.g., <strong>"shepherd"</strong>)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-4 shadow-lg">
    <div class="card-body">
      <p><strong>API URL:</strong> <a href="https://dog.ceo/api/breed/affenpinscher/images/random" class="text-info">https://dog.ceo/api/breed/affenpinscher/images/random</a></p>
      <p>This API returns a random image of a specific breed, which we will utilize to save images associated with various dog breeds. The response provides the URL of the image.</p>
      <p><strong>Table:</strong> <code>Images</code></p>
      <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Columns:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><code>url</code> - Contains the URL of the image</li>
            <li><code>breed_id</code> - Connects the image to its corresponding breed</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-4 shadow-lg">
    <div class="card-body">
      <p><strong>Faker:</strong> <code>Breed_size</code></p>
      <p>Utilizing Faker allows us to assign a size attribute to each breed.</p>
      <p><strong>Table:</strong> <code>Breeds</code></p>
      <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Columns:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><code>size</code> - Indicates the size classification of each breed</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-4 shadow-lg">
    <div class="card-header text-center bg-secondary text-white">
      <h2>Data Integration</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p>We will integrate these datasets by establishing two tables in our database: <code>Breeds</code> and <code>Images</code>. Each breed will be able to have an associated image, which we will connect through the <code>breed_id</code> in the <code>Images</code> table.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  

</div>
